About the company

Leading financial services business
New role in their Cyber team
Help build out their IAM capability

​​
About the role
This is a newly created role in a financial services who are building up an internal IAM function. Your work will be split across project related work and BAU on a yet to be determined identity platform. This could be anything from basic troubleshooting, configuration, onboarding new applications or enhancement related work. You will report into a Head of IAM who is working through product and supplier selection, the supplier will handle the design and initial implementation phase of the project.

We are looking for deep hands-on SailPoint experience. We are not seeking a Technical BA.

Culture / Benefits

Hybrid set up, results first and mature culture and environment
Work closely with "Head of" on initial implementation for the whole business
Tight knit and collaborative team


Duties

Implementation and support based work for identity products
Enhancement, onboarding, configuration and support
Stakeholder engagement internally - up to senior level
Help grow the function and team


Skills and experience

Prior experience with SailPoint
Ability to work on initial configuration and support
Enhancement experience, able to onboard new apps to the chosen solution
Strong stakeholder engagement skills and ability
​​​​​​​Exceptional communication skills - written and verbal
​​​​​​​Industry certifications are highly regarded.

Senior Data Scientist | NLP & LLM Focus | Financial Services

We're partnering with a leading financial services organisation to find a technically strong Senior Data Scientist to join their analytics function.

What We're Looking For:

You're a Data Scientist who excels at productionising models and deploying robust, scalable solutions. Your strength lies in taking NLP and LLM projects from experimentation through to production, with deep technical expertise and strong engineering fundamentals. You're pragmatic, outcomes-focused, and thrive in technical environments where quality code and reliable deployments matter.

The Technical Essentials:

Education: Master's or PhD in Data Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science or related discipline
Production Focus: Proven track record of productionising data science solutions in commercial environments
NLP Expertise: Hands-on commercial experience with modern NLP techniques-supervised learning using LSTM/CNN/Transformers, topic modelling, and production implementations
LLM & GenAI: Real-world experience deploying GPT-based solutions (langchain, llamaindex, RAG pipelines, multi-agent frameworks)
Technical Chops: Advanced SQL proficiency and strong Python development capabilities, particularly in NLP contexts
Engineering Fundamentals: Experience building, deploying, and maintaining models in production environments
Research-Minded: You stay current with the latest LLM research and can apply it practically

What Makes You Stand Out:

You're technically sharp with a strong engineering mindset. You understand the full model lifecycle and can write production-quality code. You communicate clearly enough to collaborate effectively within technical teams, are open to feedback, and comfortable operating in agile, fast-paced environments.

Job Title: Business Analyst - AI, CTP, General Insurance
Ad Text:
Business Analyst - AI and General Insurance
Company: FinXL by Randstad Digital
Location: Sydney CBD and Work from home
Immediate Start
6 Months +

About Us:

FinXL by Randstad Digital focuses on accelerating client's digital and AI transformation journeys by providing specialised skills, managed programs, and strategic consulting across various industries.

We solve complex technological and business challenges with highly talented people.

We are seeking an experienced Business Analyst - with an AI and CTP- General Insurance background.

Qualifications:

Business Analyst background
Experience in CTP, General Insurance and AI knowledge
Experience in creating rule documentation for AI agent development
Experience in validating and updating business rules
Experience in Heuristic rules: ie translating rules into structured documentation for use by the Technical Business Analyst and Machine Learning Engineer
Experience creating process documentation as required
Experience in gathering and organising business artefacts for rule conversion.
Experience in facilitating workshops and discussions to capture business rules and processes.

Next Steps

If you would like to apply to this fantastic opportunity please apply online.

Please note that due to the volume of response only short-listed candidates will be contacted.

Code: S12

You’re ready for more

You’re a proven data leader. You’ve built teams, uplifted capability, and helped business stakeholders see the real value of data. But maybe you’re stuck somewhere overly reactive, under-resourced, or unclear on direction.

You want to lead a function with purpose. You want influence, access, and the opportunity to get it right, not just maintain what’s already there.

This is that role.

You’ll step into an organisation investing heavily in technology, modernisation, and member experience. Data is one of the core pillars of a large transformation program, and you’ll be at the centre of it, shaping the future state, guiding decision-making, and creating a proactive, insight-led data culture.

The role

Reporting to the CIO, you’ll lead a combined team of data engineers and BI specialists, approximately ten people with two direct reports. Your remit spans strategy, architecture, governance, reporting, and capability uplift.

You’ll unite two teams under one operating model, redesign the Microsoft Fabric environment, and establish the frameworks, processes, and standards that will set the company up for long-term success.

You’ll work closely with executives, program leads, and external vendors across a major two-year investment program. This is not a hands-on role, but you’ll need enough depth to guide, challenge, and protect the integrity of the data environment.

The role requires someone who listens first, communicates well, and can translate technical concepts into simple, meaningful business language. Someone who can influence at senior levels without ego. Someone who can build trust quickly.

What you’ll lead

Define the enterprise data and analytics strategy and roadmap.
Bring together data engineering and BI under one clear operating model.
Redesign and uplift the Microsoft Fabric environment.
Oversee data architecture, modelling, pipelines, and integration.
Strengthen data governance, data quality, and stewardship.
Establish an enterprise reporting framework and reduce ad hoc work.
Partner with executives and transformation leaders across all program streams.
Lift organisational data literacy and champion insight-led decision-making

What you’ll bring

Strong experience leading data, BI, or analytics teams.
Deep understanding of Microsoft Fabric, Azure, Power BI, and governance frameworks.
Ability to communicate simply with senior stakeholders.
Experience shaping data strategy and improving enterprise reporting.
Calm, composed leadership style built on listening and clarity; and
A values-aligned approach and genuine interest in building capability

Why now

You’re joining at exactly the right time: the organisation is modernising its entire digital ecosystem, and data is central to the program’s success. There’s clarity of direction, strong executive support, and significant runway to build something meaningful.

You’ll work with a CIO who values communication, leadership presence, and authenticity. You’ll have influence, visibility, and the chance to leave a lasting impact on how data is used across the organisation.

You’ll also join a values-driven, people-centred environment with flexibility, development, and a clear commitment to purpose.

Salary and benefits

$200,000 - $210,000 including superannuation.
Receive not for profit salary packaging benefits.
Hybrid model: three days WFH, two days in office.
Five weeks of paid annual leave including Christmas to New Year closure.
Birthday leave and the ability to purchase additional leave.
Strong focus on learning and professional development.
CBD offices with modern facilities.

Next steps

For a confidential discussion, contact Steven Fulop at xceltium on 0418 994 446.

Every applicant will receive a prompt and respectful response.
